body:
@mvz yes exactly.

[We use the do block notation](https://github.com/opf/openproject/blob/93a4878dea1f1c3ed992109290dde8ca5552cee8/spec/features/wysiwyg/non_breaking_spaces_spec.rb#L58-L60) to run additional check when using `have_selector` matcher, and we just noticed recently that the block was never evaluated.

I expect it to evaluate the block regardless of `do..end` or `{..}` block notation being used. A bit like [rspec-mocks does for verifying arguments](https://relishapp.com/rspec/rspec-mocks/v/3-12/docs/configuring-responses/block-implementation#use-a-block-to-verify-arguments).
